					<msContents>
						<summary>Endowment of 20 <foreign>kaḻañcu</foreign>s of gold by Muvēntappiṭavūr alias Arunilai Śrī-Kṛṣṇa with the <foreign>ūrar</foreign>s of Vēḷkaḷa Veṇpākkam. Out of the 3 <foreign>kaḻañcu</foreign>s of yearly interest from this gold, 2 are endowed for the recitation of the <foreign>tiruppatiyam</foreign> ("glorious verse"), beginning with the phrase <foreign>kōlanaṟkuḻal</foreign>, on the seventh day of the festival of the temple of Āḻvāṇ (Viṣṇu) in Śrī-Govindapāṭi. The <foreign>tiruppatiyam</foreign> appears to have been composed by Muvēntappiṭavūr alias Kāyavāṉ Arunilai, the donor’s father.</summary>
					</msContents>
